{"title": "When Chinese keyboard warriors\u2019 hurt feelings spill over into real life", "tags": "asia", "timestamp": "2023-06-19", "content": "BEIJING \u2013 In recent weeks, Chinese nationals have made the news overseas for their reaction to real or perceived slights on their compatriots \u2013 one on board a Cathay Pacific flight over a blanket request, and another at Changi Airport involving purportedly bad customer service.\nThey highlight an apparently growing trend: As China grows in might on the international stage, its people are becoming more vocal about how others view or treat them."}